  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "By analogy, when prompts are input into LLMs, they automatically generate corresponding text.",
    "Regarding the second point, the behavioral model can respond to the external environment without being influenced unless it is hindered.",
    "The tendency created by habit makes future actions in similar situations easier and more effective (Dewey, 1997).",
    "Habit does not randomly respond to stimulus in the environment, rather, it employs homogenized response in similar situations.",
    "This characteristic corresponds to the homogenization of LLMs, which can consistently respond to similar or related issues in a similar way, mirroring the ability of habit to respond to familiar external environments and learn by example."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "The tendency created by habit makes future actions in similar situations easier and more effective (Dewey, 1997)."
  ]
